PURPOSE
This file defines the only allowed public claims and language
for this repository and any derivative communication.

SCOPE
Applies to:
- README.md
- docs/overview.md
- docs/pilot.md
- presentations, emails, talks, grant materials
- issue descriptions and pull requests

ALLOWED CLAIMS
- "Prototype decision support system"
- "Human-in-the-loop at all times"
- "Prevention-oriented design"
- "Requires independent validation"
- "Designed to surface early risk signals"
- "Advisory only; no automated enforcement"
- "Pilot-ready under constrained scope"

REQUIRED DISCLAIMERS
- No claims of operational deployment
- No claims of outcome guarantees
- No claims of accuracy, recall, or cost savings
- All metrics labeled as simulated or synthetic if referenced

DISALLOWED LANGUAGE
- Accuracy percentages
- Cost multipliers or dollar comparisons
- Market replacement, extinction, absorption, or dominance
- Inevitability, autonomy, or self-activation
- Enforcement, execution, takeover, or coercive framing
- Claims of being "live", "production", or "at scale"

DATA CLAIMS POLICY
- Only describe what the system is designed to evaluate
- Never describe results without ground-truth datasets
- All evaluation plans must be forward-looking

GOVERNANCE ASSERTIONS
- Human review is mandatory for all decisions
- System provides recommendations, not determinations
- Adoption requires local policy approval
- Operators retain full authority and accountability

ENFORCEMENT
Any contribution or communication that violates this file
must be revised before merge or publication.